<subSubSection id="5FC9655EFFC5FFED0392FDB6F0C5FD40" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="176C36D5FFC5FFED0392FDB6F0C5FD40" blockId="18.[151,1437,476,863]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">
<emphasis id="25A7EAC7FFC5FFED0392FDB6F068FD8C" bold="true" box="[151,287,548,575]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Discussion:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="D0D34D56FFC5FFED0222FDB7F095FD8C" authorityName="Perez" authorityYear="1895" box="[295,482,549,575]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abjecta">
<emphasis id="25A7EAC7FFC5FFED0222FDB7F095FD8C" box="[295,482,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Andrena abjecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was reported to occur in 
<collectingCountry id="6FC47645FFC5FFED000FFDB7F21EFD8C" box="[778,873,549,575]" name="Portugal" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Portugal</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="73424B24FFC5FFED0092FDB7F5FDFD8C" author="Baldock, D. &amp; Wood, T. J. &amp; Cross, I. &amp; Smit, J." box="[919,1162,549,575]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" pagination="1 - 164" refId="ref20369" refString="Baldock, D., Wood, T. J., Cross, I. &amp; Smit, J. (2018) The Bees of Portugal. Entomofauna, Supplement 22, 1 - 164." type="journal article" year="2018">
Baldock 
<emphasis id="25A7EAC7FFC5FFED00F8FDB4F547FD8C" box="[1021,1072,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">et al</emphasis>
. (2018)
</bibRefCitation>
on the basis of a single specimen. Examination of material from North Africa shows that the original Portuguese record is 
<taxonomicName id="D0D34D56FFC5FFED0638FDDBF0AFFD34" authority="Perez, 1895" authorityName="Perez" authorityYear="1895" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenuistriata">
<emphasis id="25A7EAC7FFC5FFED0638FDDBF030FD34" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Andrena tenuistriata</emphasis>
Pérez, 1895
</taxonomicName>
as the fovea are too wide and the base of the propodeal triangle is too extensively wrinkled and lacks the necessary granular microsculpture. 
<taxonomicName id="D0D34D56FFC5FFED004BFD03F572FD18" authorityName="Perez" authorityYear="1895" box="[846,1029,657,683]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Andrena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abjecta">
<emphasis id="25A7EAC7FFC5FFED004BFD03F572FD18" box="[846,1029,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Andrena abjecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could occur in 
<collectingCountry id="6FC47645FFC5FFED07ABFD03F47AFD18" box="[1198,1293,657,683]" name="Portugal" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Portugal</collectingCountry>
with records known from the neighbouring Huelva province in 
<collectingCountry id="6FC47645FFC5FFED000CFD27F23EFD7C" box="[777,841,693,719]" name="Spain" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">Spain</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="73424B24FFC5FFED005FFD27F541FD7C" author="Dardon, M. J. &amp; Torres, F. &amp; Ornosa, C." box="[858,1078,693,719]" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" pagination="467 - 497" refId="ref20799" refString="Dardon, M. J., Torres, F. &amp; Ornosa, C. (2014) The subgenus Andrena (Micrandrena) (Hymenoptera: Andrenidae) in the Iberian Peninsula. Zootaxa, 3872, 467 - 497. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3872.5.3" type="journal article" year="2014">
Dardon 
<emphasis id="25A7EAC7FFC5FFED00BCFD24F29BFD7C" box="[953,1004,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="219">et al</emphasis>
. 2014
</bibRefCitation>
) but for now its presence must remain unconfirmed.
</paragraph>
